<mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>&#8712;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8757;</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mi>&#952;</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mi>&#952;</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#62;</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>&#8712;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/15670a4f-1afb-4513-8515-25b81b592034-9896338.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 297px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Given&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#946;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>Now <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#945;</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>&#946;</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>Now defining&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>Hence <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;is&nbsp;the only possible solution</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>&#946;</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8230;</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>On solving equations <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math>&nbsp;we get,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>12</mn></mfrac></math></p>","difficulty": "Hard","source": "Top 250 Single Correct Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a70417cc3fb48d6831a","paperSource": "JEE Main 2023 (31 Jan Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Mathematics","chapter": "Trigonometry","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 250 Single Correct Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cot</mi><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>24</mn></mfrac></math> is:","options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></math>"],"answer": 1,"solution": "<p>We know that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cot</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Since,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>24</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Therefore,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cot</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mrow><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>cot</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>24</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mrow><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mfenced></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Top 250 Single Correct Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6b417cc3fb48d67396","paperSource": "JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Mathematics","chapter": "Trigonometry","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 250 Single Correct Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>cosec</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math> is a root of the equation:","options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<p>We know that&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mn>18</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>cosec</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>18</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Rationalizing denominator</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>Hence equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>5</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>","difficulty": "Easy","source": "Top 250 Single Correct Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6c417cc3fb48d676bf","paperSource": "JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Mathematics","chapter": "Trigonometry","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 250 Single Correct Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "The number of real roots of the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math> is:","options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math>"],"answer": 3,"solution": "<p>We have,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>For equation to be defined,</p><p>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math>,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8805;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>And, from domain of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8804;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math>&nbsp;from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#38;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math>&nbsp;only possibility that the equation is defined is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8800;</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>and at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>tan</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msqrt><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#8800;</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>None of these values satisfy</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math> Number&nbsp;of roots<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Top 250 Single Correct Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6a417cc3fb48d670ce","paperSource": "JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Mathematics","chapter": "Trigonometry","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 250 Single Correct Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac></math> is equal to:","options": ["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math>"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<blockquote><p>Given,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Now by we know that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mi>&#952;</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>, so by using this we get&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>22</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and similarly&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>{As&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>22</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math>}</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#960;</mi><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>32</mn><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mrow><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>4</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>11</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math></p></blockquote>","difficulty": "Hard","source": "Top 250 Single Correct Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6c417cc3fb48d6788f","paperSource": "JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 2)"}]}